It is a penetration testing process performed on the Bluemoon 2021 vulnerableVM as a part of a system
hacking lab exercise. 

1. Stage 1 - Reconnaissance 
Tool: netdiscover, nmap 

<sudo netdiscover>
<nmap -sn 192.168.1.0/24> 
- To find the victim's IP which is 192.168.1.151

2. Stage 2 - Scanning & Enumeration
Tool: gobuster, nmap, dirb

<nmap -sC -sV -Pn -vv 192.168.1.151> 
-sC > is to run default NSE scripts (service enumeration, basic vuln checks)
-sV > to detect service versions on open ports
-Pn > skip host discovery (which we assume the host is online)
-vv > very verbose output which it shows progeress and results in real time

I discovered 3 open ports which is: 
Port 21 -- FTP (vsftpd 3.0.3)
Port 22 -- SSH (OpenSSH) 
Port 80 -- HTTP (Apache) 

Run <gobuster dir> to find hidden files on a web server. 
The result scanning showed that there were to files found. 
</server_status> (403)
</hidden_text> (200)
Since the first one wasn't opened, I opened </hidden_text> 

It directed to a page where it has link, I clicked the link and it directed me to an image
which showed QR code. 
Downloaded the QR code and decode it on any website.
I found that there was a username and password. 

